WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
[Unknown]: IVM.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:34.360
[Amit Varma]: We behave as if we are subjects, not citizens.

00:00:34.360 --> 00:00:40.440
[Amit Varma]: As if the laws that exist in this country do so for the purpose of our overlords monitoring

00:00:40.440 --> 00:00:41.440
[Amit Varma]: our behaviour.

00:00:41.440 --> 00:00:44.200
[Amit Varma]: Our free speech laws are a great example of this.

00:00:44.200 --> 00:00:50.780
[Amit Varma]: Section 295A, 153A and 124A are all throwbacks from the British Empire which framed the Indian

00:00:50.780 --> 00:00:54.320
[Amit Varma]: Penal Code to keep us natives under their control.

00:00:54.320 --> 00:00:59.920
[Amit Varma]: And yet, even after independence, even 72 years after independence, we are still oppressed

00:00:59.920 --> 00:01:04.480
[Amit Varma]: by largely the same set of laws designed to keep us in check.

00:01:04.480 --> 00:01:09.020
[Amit Varma]: Section 124A, the law against sedition, is a great example of this.

00:01:09.020 --> 00:01:13.300
[Amit Varma]: It is natural for an oppressive autocratic state to have a law such as this.

00:01:13.300 --> 00:01:17.660
[Amit Varma]: But why must a responsive democracy have a sedition law?

00:01:17.660 --> 00:01:22.840
[Amit Varma]: It's actually the duty of citizens to constantly point out the flaws in our government, to

00:01:22.840 --> 00:01:24.480
[Amit Varma]: speak truth to power.

00:01:24.480 --> 00:01:29.640
[Amit Varma]: We live in times where those in power actually speak of strengthening the sedition law, where

00:01:29.640 --> 00:01:34.560
[Amit Varma]: it is used to harass dissenters and to have a chilling effect on would-be dissenters.

00:01:34.560 --> 00:01:37.520
[Amit Varma]: To speak up against this is our duty.

00:01:37.520 --> 00:01:38.520
[Amit Varma]: Is it also criminal?

00:01:38.520 --> 00:01:47.840
[Unknown]: Welcome to The Seen and The Unseen, our weekly podcast on economics, politics and behavioural

00:01:47.840 --> 00:01:48.840
[Unknown]: science.

00:01:48.840 --> 00:01:53.480
[Amit Varma]: Please welcome your host, Amit Bharma.

00:01:53.480 --> 00:01:54.920
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to The Seen and The Unseen.

00:01:54.920 --> 00:01:59.720
[Amit Varma]: My guest for today is Chitranshul Sinha, who has written a fantastic history of the sedition

00:01:59.720 --> 00:02:02.560
[Amit Varma]: law in India, Section 124A.

