[Guest]: So they had a makeshift law, when the mutiny happened, they got a makeshift law in where

00:50:46.760 --> 00:50:51.160
[Guest]: they provided for an offense against the state that which is somewhat, I won't say similar

00:50:51.160 --> 00:50:55.120
[Guest]: to sedition, but it was the first step towards having a law against sedition where you can't

00:50:55.120 --> 00:50:58.720
[Guest]: criticize the government or say anything against the government and it had to be tried.

00:50:58.720 --> 00:51:02.600
[Guest]: And there was a summary trial with no appeal provided if you did something like that.

00:51:02.600 --> 00:51:08.040
[Guest]: So when the mutiny ended, and it's called the 1857 revolution, but at the end of the

00:51:08.040 --> 00:51:14.040
[Guest]: day, it went on till 1858 and 1859, it finally ended in around 1859.

00:51:14.040 --> 00:51:16.880
[Guest]: And that's when in 1860, the new law comes in.

